            <title><![CDATA[This Week A Studio Was Shut Down, Rumble Rescued A Pariah, And Water Remained Wet]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/dr-disrespect-rumble-ps5-portable-rumors-trump-tariffs-1851710364</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/this-week-a-studio-was-shut-down-rumble-rescued-a-pariah-and-water-remained-wet.1048593/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/dr-disrespect-rumble-ps5-portable-rumors-trump-tariffs-1851710364<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="a20b120c976fd3c79bf3f8ff531f1be7" data-recommend-id="image://a20b120c976fd3c79bf3f8ff531f1be7" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Humanoid Origin<!-- -->, <!-- -->Double Barrel Games / 6side Studio / Moonsaurus Games / VEA Games / Z. Bill / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Xbox / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Wachiwit / Fox / Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- --> (<!-- -->Shutterstock<!-- -->)<!-- -->, <!-- -->Meta / Kotaku / Gleb Kosarenko<!-- --> (<!-- -->Getty Images<!-- -->)<!-- -->, <!-- -->Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Dimitar Dilkoff<!-- --> (<!-- -->Getty Images<!-- -->)<!-- -->, <!-- -->Rich Fury<!-- --> (<!-- -->Getty Images<!-- -->)<!-- -->, <!-- -->Sony<!-- -->, <!-- -->Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Tencent / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Lucasfilm / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="a20b120c976fd3c79bf3f8ff531f1be7" data-recommend-id="image://a20b120c976fd3c79bf3f8ff531f1be7" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>This may have been a short workweek, but the chaotic world of gaming never rests. Read on for <em>Kotaku</em>’s top stories from Thanksgiving week.</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="4e27b3c8afaf894bd4f4dd7b39f51560" data-recommend-id="image://4e27b3c8afaf894bd4f4dd7b39f51560" data-format="jpg" data-width="1560" data-height="880" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="People look out at ships in the sky. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="People look out at ships in the sky. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Humanoid Origin</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4e27b3c8afaf894bd4f4dd7b39f51560" data-recommend-id="image://4e27b3c8afaf894bd4f4dd7b39f51560" data-format="jpg" data-width="1560" data-height="880" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="People look out at ships in the sky. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>In 2021, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/bioware-studio-head-dragon-age-producer-both-leave-stu-1845802859&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/bioware-studio-head-dragon-age-producer-both-leave-stu-1845802859">former BioWare general manager Casey Hudson</a></span> announced a new studio called Humanoid Origin. It was working on a sci-fi blockbuster and hiring for an ambitious future. On Monday, however, the studio announced it was shutting down just a few years later, having failed to acquire the funding needed to continue.  - Ethan Gach </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/mass-effect-casey-hudson-humanoid-origin-scifi-bioware-1851707754?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/mass-effect-casey-hudson-humanoid-origin-scifi-bioware-1851707754?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="a6ed0a780ab63f7ec7ce3fc4bda3efd1" data-recommend-id="image://a6ed0a780ab63f7ec7ce3fc4bda3efd1" data-format="jpg" data-width="2400" data-height="1600" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="getty" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Dimitar Dilkoff<!-- --> (<!-- -->Getty Images<!-- -->)</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="a6ed0a780ab63f7ec7ce3fc4bda3efd1" data-recommend-id="image://a6ed0a780ab63f7ec7ce3fc4bda3efd1" data-format="jpg" data-width="2400" data-height="1600" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>In mid-2019, then-President Donald Trump <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.cnn.com/2019/05/09/business/iphones-toys-china-tariffs/index.html&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.cnn.com/2019/05/09/business/iphones-toys-china-tariffs/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">threatened to extend</a></span> existing tariffs on industrial components and other goods to popular consumer products like iPhones, laptops, and video game consoles. The big three—Microsoft, Sony, and Nintendo, long-time competitors in the gaming space—rallied together to try and fend off the incoming import taxes. - Ethan Gach </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/switch-2-ps5-prices-trump-tariffs-china-nintendo-sony-1851704901?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/switch-2-ps5-prices-trump-tariffs-china-nintendo-sony-1851704901?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="2751335175b740c5c427129edc412151" data-recommend-id="image://2751335175b740c5c427129edc412151" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot from Light of Motiram, showing a red-haired woman overlooking a valley filled with mechanical animals." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot from Light of Motiram, showing a red-haired woman overlooking a valley filled with mechanical animals." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Tencent / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="2751335175b740c5c427129edc412151" data-recommend-id="image://2751335175b740c5c427129edc412151" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot from Light of Motiram, showing a red-haired woman overlooking a valley filled with mechanical animals." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>As <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-pokemon-palworld-patents-lawsuit-pocketpair-1851692965&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-pokemon-palworld-patents-lawsuit-pocketpair-1851692965">Nintendo gears up to take down <em>Palworld</em></a></span> for its aping of <em>Pokémon</em> game design elements, another high-profile court case seems inevitable with Tencent’s announcement of <em>Light of Motiram </em>(thanks <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.gematsu.com/2024/11/mechanimal-open-world-survival-crafting-game-light-of-motiram-announced-for-pc&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/2024/11/mechanimal-open-world-survival-crafting-game-light-of-motiram-announced-for-pc" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Gematsu</em></a></span>), a game that looks uncannily similar to Sony’s <em>Horizon Zero Dawn</em>. - John Walker </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/horizon-zero-dawn-sony-light-of-motiram-tencent-copy-1851709969?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/horizon-zero-dawn-sony-light-of-motiram-tencent-copy-1851709969?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="5357b430678c13f9b4cf292c52255fdd" data-recommend-id="image://5357b430678c13f9b4cf292c52255fdd" data-format="jpg" data-width="2165" data-height="1218" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Guy Beahm talks on his phone. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Guy Beahm talks on his phone. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="getty" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Rich Fury<!-- --> (<!-- -->Getty Images<!-- -->)</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="5357b430678c13f9b4cf292c52255fdd" data-recommend-id="image://5357b430678c13f9b4cf292c52255fdd" data-format="jpg" data-width="2165" data-height="1218" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Guy Beahm talks on his phone. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>Controversial video game streamer Guy “Dr Disrespect” Beahm is officially joining Rumble, the right-wing streaming platform online personalities like Russell Brand go to <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/sep/23/firms-pull-ads-from-rumble-platform-over-russell-brand-videos&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/sep/23/firms-pull-ads-from-rumble-platform-over-russell-brand-videos" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">when no one else will have them</a></span>. The “alt-tech” platform announced the former Twitch star will receive equity and be an advisor despite admitting earlier this year to having <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dr-disrespect-sexting-twitch-ban-youtube-elden-ring-1851556854?_gl=1*vlv207*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjU0NDQ0Ny4yOS4xLjE3MzI1NTAzNjYuNTUuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dr-disrespect-sexting-twitch-ban-youtube-elden-ring-1851556854?_gl=1*vlv207*_ga*MzQzNjkwNDM2LjE2NDY2NjQ1NzQ.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjU0NDQ0Ny4yOS4xLjE3MzI1NTAzNjYuNTUuMC4w">“inappropriate” conversations with a minor</a></span> several years ago.  - Ethan Gach </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/dr-disrespect-youtube-rumble-twitch-ban-sexting-crypto-1851707478?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/dr-disrespect-youtube-rumble-twitch-ban-sexting-crypto-1851707478?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="4d89395dc7a27c671242992e0d09ce17" data-recommend-id="image://4d89395dc7a27c671242992e0d09ce17" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Five indie game screenshots, sliced and spliced together to make one mad image." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Five indie game screenshots, sliced and spliced together to make one mad image." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Double Barrel Games / 6side Studio / Moonsaurus Games / VEA Games / Z. Bill / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4d89395dc7a27c671242992e0d09ce17" data-recommend-id="image://4d89395dc7a27c671242992e0d09ce17" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Five indie game screenshots, sliced and spliced together to make one mad image." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>Once upon a time, the United States of America would enjoy a holiday called “Thanksgiving.” However, over time, as culture shifted and the country changed, it eventually evolved into the day of celebration we now all know and love. That’s right, Thanksgaming! It’s the day of the year when everyone in America—and all around the world—gets together to celebrate unknown indie games. - John Walker </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/thanksgaming-24-indie-games-wishlist-steam-1851709999?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/thanksgaming-24-indie-games-wishlist-steam-1851709999?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="efc2a7024bc78f4082d656d41ee87ae9" data-recommend-id="image://efc2a7024bc78f4082d656d41ee87ae9" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image shows Xbox avatars. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An image shows Xbox avatars. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Xbox / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="efc2a7024bc78f4082d656d41ee87ae9" data-recommend-id="image://efc2a7024bc78f4082d656d41ee87ae9" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image shows Xbox avatars. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>Microsoft has quietly confirmed that it is ditching avatars on <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/goodbye-to-the-xbox-one-the-most-pointless-console-i-h-1845692715&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/goodbye-to-the-xbox-one-the-most-pointless-console-i-h-1845692715">Xbox One</a></span> and Xbox Series X/S consoles next year after a decade of support. You might have assumed avatars had already been killed off in the past, but nope. Apparently they were still around, but not for much longer.  - Zack Zwiezen </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/xbox-avatars-editor-app-delist-series-x-s-removed-360-1851707586?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/xbox-avatars-editor-app-delist-series-x-s-removed-360-1851707586?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="42875dcf1c6dfc26cbf862212aecc435" data-recommend-id="image://42875dcf1c6dfc26cbf862212aecc435" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot of the trailer shows all the Hunters from the game. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A screenshot of the trailer shows all the Hunters from the game. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Lucasfilm / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="42875dcf1c6dfc26cbf862212aecc435" data-recommend-id="image://42875dcf1c6dfc26cbf862212aecc435" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A screenshot of the trailer shows all the Hunters from the game. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>Earlier this year, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/star-wars-hunters-review-is-it-good-switch-ps5-xbox-pc-1851521852&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/star-wars-hunters-review-is-it-good-switch-ps5-xbox-pc-1851521852"><em>Star Wars: Hunters</em></a></span><em> </em>landed on mobile devices and Switch. The free-to-play third-person hero shooter was a very fun and good game that was trapped on mobile devices. Well, except for Switch, but that port wasn’t great. Now, <em>Hunters </em>is finally making the leap to PC, alongside some visual upgrades, too.  - Zack Zwiezen </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/star-wars-hunters-pc-console-port-steam-phone-overwatch-1851708516?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/star-wars-hunters-pc-console-port-steam-phone-overwatch-1851708516?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="9e12fc4a227da00fe89c0be68b606677" data-recommend-id="image://9e12fc4a227da00fe89c0be68b606677" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Nintendo switch on an orange and blue background, with the screen showing The Simpson's Lionel Hutz." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A Nintendo switch on an orange and blue background, with the screen showing The Simpson's Lionel Hutz." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="shutterstock" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Wachiwit / Fox / Nintendo / Kotaku<!-- --> (<!-- -->Shutterstock<!-- -->)</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="9e12fc4a227da00fe89c0be68b606677" data-recommend-id="image://9e12fc4a227da00fe89c0be68b606677" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Nintendo switch on an orange and blue background, with the screen showing The Simpson's Lionel Hutz." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>Nintendo, currently predicting 2024 net sales of $8.4 billion and operating profits of $2.4 billion, is continuing its <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-piracy-lawsuit-mario-luigi-zelda-echoes-1851693898&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-piracy-lawsuit-mario-luigi-zelda-echoes-1851693898">furious</a></span> <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-yuzu-emulator-github-piracy-zelda-1851452740&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-yuzu-emulator-github-piracy-zelda-1851452740">crackdown</a></span> on those modding or emulating its systems and games. Its latest target, via a story by <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.gamefile.news/p/after-inc-plague-inc-ndemic-pandemic?open=false#%C2%A7item-nintendo-seeks-new-targets&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.gamefile.news/p/after-inc-plague-inc-ndemic-pandemic?open=false#%C2%A7item-nintendo-seeks-new-targets" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Game File</em></a></span>, is the Reddit sub SwitchPirates, while also asking to subpoena information from a vast array of companies, including Reddit, to identify those involved in so-called “Pirate Shops.” - John Walker </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-reddit-switchpirates-court-filing-1851710042?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-switch-reddit-switchpirates-court-filing-1851710042?_gl=1*b16riv*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc1OTQzLjkuMC4w">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="17d54d5845d2646fa6fbe8ec8e0d4bae" data-recommend-id="image://17d54d5845d2646fa6fbe8ec8e0d4bae" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image shows a cartoon thief looking at a VR headset. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An image shows a cartoon thief looking at a VR headset. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="getty" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Meta / Kotaku / Gleb Kosarenko<!-- --> (<!-- -->Getty Images<!-- -->)</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="17d54d5845d2646fa6fbe8ec8e0d4bae" data-recommend-id="image://17d54d5845d2646fa6fbe8ec8e0d4bae" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image shows a cartoon thief looking at a VR headset. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>A whole bunch of Oculus VR headsets were allegedly stolen by a group of men who 